Set up the Canvas and create all the Card Visualizations Part 2 8

Step 7.4 - YoY Shootings Card.


 


 

Create the following measurements:

.YOY SHO % =

VAR PYSHO =

CALCULATE([.Total Shootings], DATEADD('Calendar'[Date],-1, YEAR))

RETURN

DIVIDE(([.Total Shootings] - PYSHO), PYSHO)

 .Average YOY SHO = AVERAGEX(VALUES('Calendar'[Year]), [.YOY SHO %])+0

 .KPI Symbol SHO = if([.Average YOY SHO]>0,"?","?")

 .Concatenate SHO = COMBINEVALUES(" ",[.KPI Symbol SHO],FORMAT([.Average YOY SHO],"0.0%"))

 

It is like the previously created card. Copy the previous visual and paste it and select the following options as shown in the next pictures.

Step 7.6 – Victims Per Year Card.

Create the following measures:

.Total Victims = SUMX(DISTINCT(FactTable[ShootingID]), FIRSTNONBLANK(FactTable[TotalVictims], 0))+0

.Victims Per Year = ([.Total Victims]/((max('Calendar'[Year])-min('Calendar'[Year])+1)))+0

Copy the Shootings Per Year card and paste it.

Replace the previous field with the measure .Victims Per Year.

Change the title to Victims Per Year.


 

 


Configure the X and Y position.


 

 

 

Step 7.7 – YoY Victims Card.

 Create the following measures:

 .YOY VIC % =

VAR PYVIC =

CALCULATE([.Total Victims], DATEADD('Calendar'[Date],-1, YEAR))

RETURN

DIVIDE(([.Total Victims] - PYVIC), PYVIC)

 .Average YOY VIC = AVERAGEX(VALUES('Calendar'[Year]), [.YOY VIC %])+0

 .KPI Symbol VIC = if([.Average YOY VIC]>0,"?","?")

 .Concatenate VIC = COMBINEVALUES(" ",[.KPI Symbol VIC],FORMAT([.Average YOY VIC],"0.0%"))

 Copy the YoY Shootings visualization and paste it.

 Replace the previous field with the measure .Concatenate VIC


Change the title to YoY Victims.

 

 



Configure the X and Y position.
